    {
      "id": 100619316,
      "date": "2026-04-05",
      "name": "Endurance #2",
      "type": "WORKOUT",
      "sport_type": "Ride",
      "planned_tss": 53,
      "duration_hours": 1.04,
      "duration_formatted": "1h2m30s",
      "workout_summary": "6m @122W | 1m @101W | 1m @221W | 2m @101W | 3m @142W | 4m @182W | 3m @101W | 4m @132W | 2\u00d710s @304W / 4m rec | 10s @304W | 4m @132W | 10s @304W | 4m @132W | 10s @304W | 5m @122W",
      "description": "Long, low-intensity efforts aren't the only method to build endurance. Incorporating short surges into a steady effort will increase your oxygen uptake and training stimulus.\n\nCompleting a low-intensity effort with a surge every 4 minutes should feel comfortable, but the constant change in power and surging will provide you with significant gains in endurance.\n\nWarmup\n- 30^ We begin the warm up with a gentle aerobic effort.<!> 6m ramp 44.9-75%\n\n- 50^ Now for a 1min high power, effort.<!> 1m 50%\n- 1m 109%\n- 110^ To prepare for the efforts we step up to a 4min sub-threshold effort now.<!> 2m 50%\n\nWarmup\n- 150^ Nearly at sub-threshold power now. 170^ Time for the 4min sub-threshold effort.<!> 3m ramp 50-89.9%\n\n- 4m 89.9%\n- 100^ Long, low intensity efforts aren't the only way to build endurance. 120^ Incorporating short surges into your effort will increase oxygen uptake and training stimulus.<!> 3m 50%\n\n100^ Completing a low intensity effort with a surge every 4 minutes should feel comfortable 120^ The constant change in power and surging, will provide you with big gains in endurance. 230^ Ready for the 1st surge.<!> 2x\n- 4m ramp 56-75%\n- 10s 150%\n- 10^ Back to low aerobic power now.<!> 4m ramp 56-75%\n- 10s 150%\n\nWarmup\n- 4m ramp 56-75%\n\n2x\n- 10s 150%\n- 20^ Just 4 more surges to go. 40^ Still feel comfortable?<!> 4m ramp 56-75%\n\n- 10s 150%\n\nWarmup\n- 30^ This is a low intensity session that provides great aerobic gains. 40^ The kind of session that could be used weekly as your endurance day.<!> 4m ramp 56-75%\n\n- 10s 150%\n\nWarmup\n- 230^ Into the last surge now, then we cool down.<!> 4m ramp 56-75%\n\n- 10s 150%\n\nCooldown\n- 5m ramp 75-44.9%"
    },
